{"title_page": "Andrew Jack (dialect coach)", "text_new": "{{short description|British voice coach}}\n{{Infobox writer\n| name = Andrew Jack\n| image = \n| caption = \n| pseudonym = \n| birth_name = Andrew Hutchinson\n| birth_date = {{birth date|1944|1|28|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[London]], [[England]], UK\n| death_date = {{death date and age|2020|3|31|1946|1|28|df=y}}\n| death_place = [[UK]]\n| occupation = [[Dialect coach]], [[Hip hop]]\n| nationality = British\n| ethnicity = \n| citizenship = United Kingdom\n| education = \n| alma_mater = \n| period = 1982&ndash;2020\n| genre = \n| subject = \n| movement = \n| notableworks = \n| spouse = * Felicity Hutchinson (1974\u20131987) \n* Paula Jack (2000\u20132018)\n* Gabrielle Rogers (2019\u2013Present)\n| partner = \n| children = Rupert, Katherine Morgan (sister)<br/>{{Death date and age|2017|9|4|1989|5|4}}\n| relatives = \n| influences = \n| influenced = \n| awards = \n| signature = \n| website = {{URL|http://www.andrewjack.com}}\n| portaldisp = \n| resting_place = [[UK]]\n}}\n'''Andrew Jack''' (born '''Andrew Hutchinson''' on 28 January 1944  in [[London]], [[England]] \u2013 31 March 2020) was a British [[dialect coach]] who has worked on over 80 motion pictures since 1982.<ref>{{cite news| url=https://movies.nytimes.com/person/408903/Andrew-Jack?scp=1&sq=andrew%20jack&st=cse | work=The New York Times | title=Andrew Jack}}</ref><ref>[https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0413087/]</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nJack's father was the actor of Stephen Jack, and his mother Julia Hutchinson was a horticulturist.{{Citation needed|date=November 2017}}\n\n==Career==\nHe has worked with over 200 actors<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.andrewjack.com/artistes-actors-actresses.htm |title=Archived copy |accessdate=8 July 2011 |url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110703060353/http://www.andrewjack.com/artistes-actors-actresses.htm |archivedate=3 July 2011 }}</ref> including [[Robert Downey Jr.]] (in [[Richard Attenborough]]'s ''[[Chaplin (film)|Chaplin]]'', [[Michael Hoffman (American director)|Michael Hoffman]]'s ''[[Restoration (1995 film)|Restoration]]'' and [[Guy Ritchie]]'s ''[[Sherlock Holmes (2009 film)|Sherlock Holmes]]''), [[Pierce Brosnan]] (in ''[[GoldenEye]]'', ''[[Tomorrow Never Dies]]'' and ''[[Die Another Day]]''), [[Cate Blanchett]] and [[Viggo Mortensen]].  As supervising dialect coach for ''[[The Lord of the Rings (film series)|The Lord of the Rings]]'', he created the [[Middle-earth]] accents and taught them, along with [[Elvish]] and [[Black Speech]], to the cast of the trilogy.<ref>{{cite journal|last=Moore|first=Miranda|title=How Elijah Wood learned Elvish|journal=[[The Linguist]]|date=Feb\u2013Mar 2002}}</ref>  He designed and taught the accents for the Greeks and [[Trojan language|Trojans]] in [[Wolfgang Petersen]]'s ''[[Troy (film)|Troy]]''. He taught [[Evan Davis]] to speak with a Nottinghamshire twang.<ref>{{cite news|last=Davis|first=Evan|title=Can Evan do a Robin Hood Accent?|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/today/hi/today/newsid_8680000/8680097.stm|accessdate=8 July 2011|publisher=BBC News|date=14 May 2010}}</ref> He is known for helping non-British actors to be more intelligible to the audience.<ref>{{cite news|last=Graydon|first=Nicola|title=The Lion Roars|newspaper=The Times|date=31 May 2004}}</ref>\n\nJack can also be seen in the [[Star Wars|''Star Wars'' film series]] portraying [[Resistance (Star Wars)|Resistance]] Major (later promoted to General) [[Caluan Ematt]] in ''[[Star Wars: The Force Awakens]]'' and ''[[Star Wars: The Last Jedi]]''.\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Jack, Andrew}}\n[[Category:1944 births]]\n[[Category:2020 deaths]]\n[[Category:British voice coaches]]\n[[Category:Film people from London]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|British voice coach}}\n{{Infobox writer\n| name         = Andrew Jack\n| image        =\n| caption      = \n| pseudonym    = \n| birth_name    = Andrew Hutchinson\n| birth_date    = {{birth date|1944|1|28|df=y}}\n| birth_place   = [[London]], [[England]], UK\n| death_date    = {{death date and age|2020|3|31|1944|1|28|df=y}}\n| death_place   = [[UK]]\n| occupation   = [[Dialect coach]]\n| nationality  = British\n| ethnicity    = \n| citizenship  = United Kingdom\n| education    = \n| alma_mater   = \n| period       = 1982&ndash;2020\n| subject      = \n| movement     = \n| notableworks = \n| spouse       = * Felicity Hutchinson (1974\u20131987) \n* Paula Jack (2000\u20132018)\n* Gabrielle Rogers (2019\u20132020)\n| partner      = \n| children     = Rupert Hutchinson, Katherine Morgan\n| relatives    = \n| influences   = \n| influenced   = \n| awards       = \n| signature    = \n| website      = {{URL|http://www.andrewjack.com}}\n| portaldisp   = \n}}\n'''Andrew Jack''' (born '''Andrew Hutchinson''' on 28 January 1944  in [[London]], [[England]] \u2013 31 March 2020) was a British [[dialect coach]] who had worked on over 80 motion pictures since 1982.<ref>{{cite news| url=https://movies.nytimes.com/person/408903/Andrew-Jack?scp=1&sq=andrew%20jack&st=cse | work=The New York Times | title=Andrew Jack}}</ref><ref>[https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0413087/]</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nJack's father was the actor of Stephen Jack, and his mother Julia Hutchinson was a horticulturist.{{Citation needed|date=November 2017}}\n\n==Career==\nHe has worked with over 200 actors<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.andrewjack.com/artistes-actors-actresses.htm |title=Archived copy |accessdate=8 July 2011 |url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110703060353/http://www.andrewjack.com/artistes-actors-actresses.htm |archivedate=3 July 2011 }}</ref> including [[Robert Downey Jr.]] (in [[Richard Attenborough]]'s ''[[Chaplin (film)|Chaplin]]'', [[Michael Hoffman (American director)|Michael Hoffman]]'s ''[[Restoration (1995 film)|Restoration]]'' and [[Guy Ritchie]]'s ''[[Sherlock Holmes (2009 film)|Sherlock Holmes]]''), [[Pierce Brosnan]] (in ''[[GoldenEye]]'', ''[[Tomorrow Never Dies]]'' and ''[[Die Another Day]]''), [[Cate Blanchett]] and [[Viggo Mortensen]].  As supervising dialect coach for ''[[The Lord of the Rings (film series)|The Lord of the Rings]]'', he created the [[Middle-earth]] accents and taught them, along with [[Elvish]] and [[Black Speech]], to the cast of the trilogy.<ref>{{cite journal|last=Moore|first=Miranda|title=How Elijah Wood learned Elvish|journal=[[The Linguist]]|date=Feb\u2013Mar 2002}}</ref>  He designed and taught the accents for the Greeks and [[Trojan language|Trojans]] in [[Wolfgang Petersen]]'s ''[[Troy (film)|Troy]]''. He taught [[Evan Davis]] to speak with a Nottinghamshire twang.<ref>{{cite news|last=Davis|first=Evan|title=Can Evan do a Robin Hood Accent?|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/today/hi/today/newsid_8680000/8680097.stm|accessdate=8 July 2011|publisher=BBC News|date=14 May 2010}}</ref> He is known for helping non-British actors to be more intelligible to the audience.<ref>{{cite news|last=Graydon|first=Nicola|title=The Lion Roars|newspaper=The Times|date=31 May 2004}}</ref>\n\nJack can also be seen in the [[Star Wars|''Star Wars'' film series]] portraying [[Resistance (Star Wars)|Resistance]] Major (later promoted to General) [[Caluan Ematt]] in ''[[Star Wars: The Force Awakens]]'' and ''[[Star Wars: The Last Jedi]]''.\n\nHe died in March 2020 from [[Covid-19]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Rest in Peace Andrew Jack, Major Caluan Ematt |url=https://www.fanthatracks.com/news/conventions-events/rest-in-peace-andrew-jack-major-caluan-ematt/ |publisher=Fantha Tracks |accessdate=31 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Jack, Andrew}}\n[[Category:1944 births]]\n[[Category:2020 deaths]]\n[[Category:British voice coaches]]\n[[Category:Film people from London]]\n[[Category:Deaths from the 2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United Kingdom]]\n", "name_user": "AnGellaMunoz", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Andrew_Jack_(dialect_coach)"}
